{"TopicId":156776,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"TRAPPIST-1 now has seven planets. (Possible life?)","CreatedByName":"_Augustus_","CreatedById":115084,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-20T22:28:11Z","PageNum":11,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-11T21:14:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223146051\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156776\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221502485591\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176924\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cabbink\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Cabbink said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny aliens there would be much more advanced.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf it even developed intelligent life, unless there\u0027s a stay at home civilization.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ProtoJeb21","CreatedById":153551,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-11T21:52:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223146056\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156776\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221502486057\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n35 minutes ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf it even developed intelligent life, unless there\u0027s a stay at home civilization.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d say that this new age estimate gives the Trappist planets a great time period for the development of life. At 5 to 10 billion years old, any life would have a very long time to adapt to atmospheric changes, low starlight, and frequent flares. Also, this would be a great amount of time for planets to rebuild any lost atmosphere through volcanism and the release of water from their mantles (like with Earth).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"insert_name","CreatedById":150339,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-31T19:47:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNASA has found evidence of water!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.popularmechanics.com/space/a28018/hubble-spots-possible-evidence-of-water-on-earth-sized-trappist-1-planets/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.popularmechanics.com/space/a28018/hubble-spots-possible-evidence-of-water-on-earth-sized-trappist-1-planets/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"_Augustus_","CreatedById":115084,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-31T21:06:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223161828\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156776\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221504208827\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150339\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022insert_name\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, insert_name said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNASA has found evidence of water!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.popularmechanics.com/space/a28018/hubble-spots-possible-evidence-of-water-on-earth-sized-trappist-1-planets/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.popularmechanics.com/space/a28018/hubble-spots-possible-evidence-of-water-on-earth-sized-trappist-1-planets/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can\u0027t wait for JWST to look at this system. I actually believe it has life now....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cabbink","CreatedById":176924,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-31T21:32:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223161908\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156776\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221504213566\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022115084\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022_Augustus_\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n25 minutes ago, _Augustus_ said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can\u0027t wait for JWST to look at this system. I actually believe it has life now....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYe.\u003Cbr\u003E\nNow if we start finding massive ammounts of gasses like methane, then we know life (or special minerals) are there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mitchz95","CreatedById":82292,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-01T22:07:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs Webb actually scheduled to look at this system? I assume there are a lot of candidates to choose from.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ProtoJeb21","CreatedById":153551,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-01T22:17:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223162792\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156776\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221504303623\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002282292\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Mitchz95\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, Mitchz95 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs Webb actually scheduled to look at this system? I assume there are a lot of candidates to choose from.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes. One of its first exoplanet targets will be TRAPPIST-1e. I assume the other planets won\u0027t be far behind.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ProtoJeb21","CreatedById":153551,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-01T22:32:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223161828\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156776\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221504208827\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150339\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022insert_name\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/31/2017 at 3:47 PM, insert_name said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNASA has found evidence of water!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.popularmechanics.com/space/a28018/hubble-spots-possible-evidence-of-water-on-earth-sized-trappist-1-planets/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.popularmechanics.com/space/a28018/hubble-spots-possible-evidence-of-water-on-earth-sized-trappist-1-planets/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s great news! This is also backed up by the most likely formation theory of the Trappist planets, which states that they started with significant amounts of water ice before migrating closer to the star. The densities of some planets, including Irene (f) and Carphos (g) suggest significant amounts of water, as in anywhere from 0.1 to 50%, depending on what mass results you\u0027re looking at. However, these diffuse hydrogen clouds don\u0027t rule out the possibility of water on Theros (b). Why? Both results for its mass suggest a low density only possible by a quarter of the planet\u0027s mass being liquid water. It\u0027s possible that Theros has lost a good portion of its original mass into space and once was a bit larger.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cabbink","CreatedById":176924,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-02T01:30:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223162810\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156776\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221504305165\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153551\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ProtoJeb21\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, ProtoJeb21 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s possible that Theros has lost a good portion of its original mass into space and once was a bit larger.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWater giant, perhaps? Maybe \u00A0water world\u00A0collided?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ProtoJeb21","CreatedById":153551,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-02T02:05:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223162916\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156776\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221504315803\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176924\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cabbink\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n34 minutes ago, Cabbink said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWater giant, perhaps? Maybe \u00A0water world\u00A0collided?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMore of a regular ocean world. I only use the phrase \u0022Water Giant\u0022 for likely ocean planets that are 1.6 Re and larger.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mitchz95","CreatedById":82292,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-02T06:24:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf there\u0027s any truth to the theory of panspermia, I wouldn\u0027t be surprised if two or more of those planets are habitable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr even inhabited... a system that densely packed would be a space-faring civilization\u0027s wet dream. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scotius","CreatedById":57622,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-02T14:19:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf we\u0027d find life on Europa and Enceladus (or Mars of course - i\u0027m still holding on to hope for some methane producing microbes)... well, then \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E I\u0027d say chances of TRAPPIST system bearing life are sky high.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ProtoJeb21","CreatedById":153551,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-02T23:49:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/115084-_augustus_/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022115084\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/115084-_augustus_/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@_Augustus_\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/176924-cabbink/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022176924\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/176924-cabbink/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Cabbink\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/150339-insert_name/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022150339\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/150339-insert_name/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@insert_name\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/152800-spaceception/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022152800\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/152800-spaceception/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Spaceception\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/82292-mitchz95/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002282292\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/82292-mitchz95/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Mitchz95\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57622-scotius/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257622\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57622-scotius/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Scotius\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Wait a minute...I just realized something.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHubble was able to detect spare clouds of hydrogen around the inner Trappist planets, which were likely created from water vapor being broken apart by X-rays. Now, since the hydrogen from H2O is lost into space, where did the oxygen go? Answer: it stayed in the planets\u0027 atmospheres. These worlds - most likely Theros - could have atmospheres rich in abiotic oxygen! This could also make conditions for life on Theros even more possible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-03T00:14:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/153551-protojeb21/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022153551\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/153551-protojeb21/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@ProtoJeb21\u003C/a\u003ETrue, but it may also lead to a false positive on our end. But it is really cool.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cabbink","CreatedById":176924,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-03T02:23:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223163569\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156776\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221504396153\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153551\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ProtoJeb21\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, ProtoJeb21 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/115084-_augustus_/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022115084\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/115084-_augustus_/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@_Augustus_\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/176924-cabbink/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022176924\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/176924-cabbink/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Cabbink\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/150339-insert_name/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022150339\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/150339-insert_name/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@insert_name\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/152800-spaceception/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022152800\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/152800-spaceception/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Spaceception\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/82292-mitchz95/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002282292\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/82292-mitchz95/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Mitchz95\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57622-scotius/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257622\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57622-scotius/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Scotius\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Wait a minute...I just realized something.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHubble was able to detect spare clouds of hydrogen around the inner Trappist planets, which were likely created from water vapor being broken apart by X-rays. Now, since the hydrogen from H2O is lost into space, where did the oxygen go? Answer: it stayed in the planets\u0027 atmospheres. These worlds - most likely Theros - could have atmospheres rich in abiotic oxygen! This could also make conditions for life on Theros even more possible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nForget proxima centauri. \u00A0Send starshot to trappist 1.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould we use gravity assists to slow down? I mean, it\u0027s 7 planets.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-03T02:43:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223163635\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156776\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221504405419\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176924\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cabbink\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 minutes ago, Cabbink said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nForget proxima centauri. \u00A0Send starshot to trappist 1.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould we use gravity assists to slow down? I mean, it\u0027s 7 planets.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNah, from 1/5 the speed of light? You\u0027d have to have a laser array on the other side to have a chance.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlus it\u0027d take around 200 years, so there\u0027s that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-09-03T02:43:20Z\u0022 title=\u002209/03/2017 02:43  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 3, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Spaceception\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cabbink","CreatedById":176924,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-03T02:45:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223163641\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156776\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221504406582\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNah, from 1/5 the speed of light? You\u0027d have to have a laser array on the other side to have a chance.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlus it\u0027d take around 200 years, so there\u0027s that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh yeah. Forgot about that\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe need exotic or negative\u00A0matter stat. We need some warp drives.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cabbink","CreatedById":176924,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-03T03:24:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nanyways, here\u0027s a banner from the solar system art thing. Not going to\u00A0link or any thing. I\u0027m going to re-use it for this thread as a banner. I\u0027ll have an edit for this when I get to it . They are even properly scaled to eachother (somewhat)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWarning. Massive photo\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022uoxWoYm.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022204\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/uoxWoYm.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-09-03T03:25:04Z\u0022 title=\u002209/03/2017 03:25  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 3, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Cabbink\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scotius","CreatedById":57622,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-03T05:20:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223163569\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156776\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221504396153\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153551\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ProtoJeb21\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, ProtoJeb21 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/115084-_augustus_/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022115084\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/115084-_augustus_/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@_Augustus_\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/176924-cabbink/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022176924\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/176924-cabbink/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Cabbink\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/150339-insert_name/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022150339\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/150339-insert_name/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@insert_name\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/152800-spaceception/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022152800\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/152800-spaceception/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Spaceception\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/82292-mitchz95/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002282292\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/82292-mitchz95/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Mitchz95\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57622-scotius/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257622\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57622-scotius/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Scotius\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Wait a minute...I just realized something.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHubble was able to detect spare clouds of hydrogen around the inner Trappist planets, which were likely created from water vapor being broken apart by X-rays. Now, since the hydrogen from H2O is lost into space, where did the oxygen go? Answer: it stayed in the planets\u0027 atmospheres. These worlds - most likely Theros - could have atmospheres rich in abiotic oxygen! This could also make conditions for life on Theros even more possible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor Earthlike life it wouldn\u0027t be good news. First microbes that appeared on our planet were anaerobes - oxygen, despite being a byproduct of their metabolism, was toxic to them. Switch to oxygen - based metabolism processes happened only when life was well established, and rightfully is called an Oxygen Revolution.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ProtoJeb21","CreatedById":153551,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-03T11:55:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223163708\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156776\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221504416028\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257622\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scotius\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, Scotius said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor Earthlike life it wouldn\u0027t be good news. First microbes that appeared on our planet were anaerobes - oxygen, despite being a byproduct of their metabolism, was toxic to them. Switch to oxygen - based metabolism processes happened only when life was well established, and rightfully is called an Oxygen Revolution.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI find it unlikely that Earth-like life could develop on Theros at all, considering how most of the planet is likely covered in one giant sauna hundreds of kilometers deep. However, the possibility of oxygen in the atmosphere is promising for the development of some life forms...if there\u0027s any land on this planet. There could be giant floating salt islands caused by the evaporation of water that left behind trapped salt. Honestly, it really depends on how deep Theros\u0027 oceans are, which will determine if any land is present and what chemicals will be in the water.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cabbink","CreatedById":176924,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-03T15:09:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223163839\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156776\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221504439716\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153551\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ProtoJeb21\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, ProtoJeb21 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI find it unlikely that Earth-like life could develop on Theros at all, considering how most of the planet is likely covered in one giant sauna hundreds of kilometers deep. However, the possibility of oxygen in the atmosphere is promising for the development of some life forms...if there\u0027s any land on this planet. There could be giant floating salt islands caused by the evaporation of water that left behind trapped salt. Honestly, it really depends on how deep Theros\u0027 oceans are, which will determine if any land is present and what chemicals will be in the water.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about bacteria ? Islands made of massive swaths of microorganisms? \u00A0How about that as land? Or whale \u00A0islands?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scotius","CreatedById":57622,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-03T18:45:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223163953\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156776\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221504451371\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176924\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cabbink\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Cabbink said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about bacteria ? Islands made of massive swaths of microorganisms? \u00A0How about that as land? Or whale \u00A0islands?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E. Unless it\u0027s some sort of floating, porous reef less dense than surrounding it water and covered in a milimeters thick \u0022skin\u0022 of microorganisms. For more complicated structures you would need circulatory system, something akin to gills or lungs, digestive system, skeleton supporting all of this etc. It would be a proper animal by then - and multicellular organisms aren\u0027t easy to create \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E On Earth evolution needed hundreds of millions of years to go from amoebas to jellyfish and corals.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"UranianBlue","CreatedById":174952,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-06T19:30:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyeah, apart from the tidal locking, intense radiation from TRAPPIST-1, it will be great! Now, astronomers just need to see what\u0027s in the atmosphere of these planets (if they have any). That will tell us the difference from an exo-Venus and an exo-Earth!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ProtoJeb21","CreatedById":153551,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-06T21:56:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think it may be a bit too early to reveal this...but there might be an EIGHTH planet of Trappist-1.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cabbink","CreatedById":176924,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-06T22:01:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223166752\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156776\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221504735017\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153551\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ProtoJeb21\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n22 minutes ago, ProtoJeb21 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think it may be a bit too early to reveal this...but there might be an EIGHTH planet of Trappist-1.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSaw the is on EE. It orbits far, Like h,\u00A0right? Do you\u00A0know how big it is, or what it\u0027s composition might be?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-09-06T22:19:48Z\u0022 title=\u002209/06/2017 10:19  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 6, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Cabbink\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}